1
00:00:05,809 --> 00:00:08,579
We say, "Well, in dealing 
with other people

2
00:00:08,579 --> 00:00:10,299
what is the general rule?"

3
00:00:10,299 --> 00:00:15,098
Tṛṇād api sunīcena,
taror api sahiṣṇunā,
amāninā mānadena...

4
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:18,023
to be humble, tolerant,
offer respect to others.

5
00:00:18,023 --> 00:00:21,518
[Armed with Humility]

6
00:00:21,518 --> 00:00:29,063
But when some ignorant 
people heard,

7
00:00:29,063 --> 00:00:32,635
thinking that the Mayapur
Chandradaya Mandir

8
00:00:32,635 --> 00:00:34,258
there are so many 
Americans there,

9
00:00:34,258 --> 00:00:36,859
and they have so much money.
The rumours spread that

10
00:00:36,859 --> 00:00:40,973
the Deity was made
out of gold, solid gold.

11
00:00:41,843 --> 00:00:46,073
So they wanted 
to steal Radharani

12
00:00:46,618 --> 00:00:49,538
and maybe Krishna,
They are both, like that,

13
00:00:49,724 --> 00:00:51,794
they heard, "They are solid gold".

14
00:00:51,837 --> 00:00:52,959
And when they came,

15
00:00:52,959 --> 00:00:54,799
the leaders of the time

16
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:56,821
defended the Deities

17
00:00:56,988 --> 00:00:59,768
even... with weapons.

18
00:01:00,047 --> 00:01:02,674
So some people came
to Guru Maharaj,

19
00:01:02,674 --> 00:01:03,634
and they said,

20
00:01:03,732 --> 00:01:07,502
"They are not following
Mahaprabhu's teachings

21
00:01:08,494 --> 00:01:10,144
of being humble, tolerant

22
00:01:10,144 --> 00:01:12,671
and offering respect to others.

23
00:01:13,651 --> 00:01:16,901
But Guru Maharaj said,
"No, I supported them, saying,

24
00:01:17,801 --> 00:01:22,245
'Tṛṇād api sunīcena to who?'

25
00:01:22,784 --> 00:01:26,904
That you've come to molest
the Deity and the Vaishnava,

26
00:01:26,904 --> 00:01:29,764
and then I will practice humility?"

27
00:01:30,265 --> 00:01:31,689
He said, "No, with full force

28
00:01:31,689 --> 00:01:35,929
I will defend the Deity, 
the Vaishnava".

29
00:01:38,803 --> 00:01:42,915
So, again, there is 
the famous saying,

30
00:01:42,915 --> 00:01:44,835
"ācāryavān puruṣo veda"—

31
00:01:44,891 --> 00:01:47,741
"One who's in connection 
with an acharya,

32
00:01:48,095 --> 00:01:50,615
knows what is what".

33
00:01:51,006 --> 00:01:54,856
Otherwise, if we lack 
discerning ability,

34
00:01:54,885 --> 00:01:58,145
discriminating ability

35
00:01:58,802 --> 00:02:01,202
or are not in connection

36
00:02:01,318 --> 00:02:04,948
with someone, 
who has such ability,

37
00:02:05,264 --> 00:02:10,344
then we will be likely 
to misjudge, misread.

38
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:13,655
So then it would 
be better for us

39
00:02:13,918 --> 00:02:16,918
to just be generally 
respectful

40
00:02:16,918 --> 00:02:20,336
and not make such 
determinations.

